! In analytic geometry, the centroid of a set of points is a point in the
! same domain as the set. The centroid point is chosen to show a property
! which can be calculated for that set.
! 
! Consider the centroid defined as the arithmetic mean of a set of points
! of arbitrary dimension.
! 
! Task:
! 
! Create a function in your chosen programming language to calculate such
! a centroid using an arbitrary number of points of arbitrary dimension.
! 
! ;; Test your function with the following groups of points:
! 
! one-dimensional: (1), (2), (3)
! 
! two-dimensional: (8, 2), (0, 0)
! 
! three-dimensional: the set (5, 5, 0), (10, 10, 0) and the set (1, 3.1, 6.5), (-2, -5, 3.4), (-7, -4, 9), (2, 0, 3)
! 
! five-dimensional: (0, 0, 0, 0, 1), (0, 0, 0, 1, 0), (0, 0, 1, 0, 0), (0, 1, 0, 0, 0)
! 
